Career Progression and Promotion Gap Analysis for Retention Optimization at Palo Alto Networks
Detailed guide and project requirements for the Career Progression and Promotion Gap Analysis for Retention Optimization at Palo Alto Networks analysis.

Background and Context:
Many employees leave not because of immediate dissatisfaction, but due to:

• Long gaps between promotions
• Stagnation in the same role
• Limited skill growth or training
• Weak managerial continuity
Traditional attrition models flag who may leave, but they do not explain:
What structural career issues are pushing employees toward that decision?
This project addresses this gap by focusing on career trajectory intelligence

Unified Mentor
Palo Alto Networks
Problem Statement
Palo Alto Networks currently lacks:

• A data-driven view of career progression patterns
• Identification of employees experiencing promotion stagnation
• Early signals of retention opportunity, even before disengagement
Without this, retention actions are often generic, not tailored to individual career needs.

