Data Science Methodology (Step-by-Step)
Feature Engineering
Create derived metrics such as:

• Promotion Gap Ratio = YearsSinceLastPromotion / YearsAtCompany
• Role Stagnation Index = YearsInCurrentRole / YearsAtCompany
• Training Intensity Score = TrainingTimesLastYear / YearsAtCompany
• Manager Stability Indicator
Data Preprocessing
• Normalize numerical career features
• Encode categorical fields (department, role)
• Remove extreme outliers (late-career edge cases)
Career Path Clustering (Unsupervised Learning)
• Apply clustering algorithms:
● K-Means (primary) and Hierarchical clustering (validation)
• Clusters may represent:
● Fast-track performers
● Stable long-term contributors and Early-career explorers
● Promotion-stalled employees and High-risk stagnation profiles
Cluster Interpretation & Labeling
Each cluster is analyzed and labeled based on:

• Promotion frequency
• Role change velocity
• Training participation
• Manager continuity
Promotion Gap Risk Scoring
For each employee:

• Assign a Promotion Gap Score (Low / Medium / High)
• Combine cluster membership with stagnation indicators
Retention Opportunity Identification
Identify employees who:

• Are not yet disengaged
• Are not high attrition risk
• But show career stagnation signals
